{
  "text": "In the nonhomogeneous case g(x) \u2261 0, we improve the existence result established by Wang, Ma and Wang [CITATION_1] since we relax condition (V ) by (V), skip (V ) and recover compactness by the different requirement ( f 2 ) involving r weights. Furthermore, we do not impose any sign condition on g. ",
